I was trying to propose fork blocks for London, and I just noticed an error I had made in timing schedule (https://github.com/ethereum/pm/issues/245#issuecomment-825751460): both Goerli and Rinkeby are scheduled for a fork on the same day (June 23). 

Given that due to the difficulty bomb, the mainnet fork has to stay pretty fixed, we can either:

1Ô∏è‚É£ Fork both Rinkeby and Goerli on the same day;
2Ô∏è‚É£ Fork Rinkeby and Goerli a few days apart (e.g. target Tuesday for Rinkeby and Thursday for Goerli);
3Ô∏è‚É£ Move back the first testnet fork one week, so that each network forks one week apart. This would move back the first testnet fork to June 9. 

What option do people prefer?
